      <title>Season to Taste</title>
      <itunes:author>America's Test Kitchen</itunes:author>
      <itunes:subtitle>Host Christopher Kimball interviews Molly Birnbaum, author of Season to Taste: How I Lost My Sense of Smell and Found My Way.</itunes:subtitle>
      <itunes:summary>This time on America’s Test Kitchen Radio, host Christopher Kimball interviews Molly Birnbaum. Birnbaum is the author of Season to Taste,  a book about how she lost her sense of smell. We’ll be tasting lemon  juice substitutes, and we’ll find out what’s hot and what’s not in the  world of kitchen gadgets. Then we’ll travel back in time to discover the  origins of lemon icebox cheesecake, and we’ll determine how to make the  best scrambled eggs. And of course we’ll be taking your calls to answer  all of your cooking questions.</itunes:summary>
